# IfcPipeline control-plane: always use the host-lan overlay

This is a **multi-host** stack. The control plane (redis, postgres, minio,
api-gateway) runs on the primary VM (`PIPELINE_LAN_IP=192.168.101.195`). Remote
workers on `bimbotw1` (`192.168.109.54`) reach redis/postgres/minio over the LAN.

`docker-compose.host-lan.yml` adds the `PIPELINE_LAN_IP:*` port bindings. The
base `docker-compose.yml` does **not**. So any `docker compose up -d` run
**without** the overlay makes Compose "converge" redis/minio/postgres back to
loopback-only — it **recreates them and strips the LAN bindings**, and every
remote worker breaks with `Error 111 ... Connection refused`.

## Rule

On the primary host, **every** `docker compose up -d` / `build`+`up` that can
touch the control plane MUST include both files:

```bash
cd /home/bimbot-ubuntu/apps/ifcpipeline
docker compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.host-lan.yml up -d <service>
```

This applies even when targeting one unrelated service (e.g. `api-gateway`),
because Compose still reconciles its dependencies.

## Verify after any recreate

```bash
docker ps --format '{{.Names}}: {{.Ports}}' | grep -E 'ifcpipeline-(redis|minio)|postgres_objectstorage'
# redis + minio must show 192.168.101.195; postgres must show 192.168.101.195:5432
```

## Recovery if LAN bindings were stripped

```bash
docker compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.host-lan.yml up -d redis postgres minio
# then on bimbotw1, restart any worker stuck in reconnect backoff:
# docker compose -f docker-compose.remote-workers.yml --env-file .env.remote restart <worker>
```

`DOCKER-USER` iptables allow-rules persist across recreates; only the published
ports vanish, so re-applying the overlay is enough.

## Firewall rules must be scoped to the external NIC

`DOCKER-USER` is in the FORWARD chain and (with `bridge-nf-call-iptables=1`)
also sees container-to-container traffic. Lock the LAN ports to the worker VM
**scoped to the external interface** (`eth0`) — an interface-agnostic
`--dport DROP` silently drops internal `api-gateway/n8n -> postgres/redis`
(connections time out; n8n crash-loops). Apply/repair with:

```bash
sudo ./scripts/apply-host-lan-firewall.sh
```
